# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║   UAIS  v28  —  Unified AI Intelligence System  [Production]                       ║
# ║   Single-file bootstrapper · scaffolds full workspace · Apache 2.0             ║
# ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   ⚑  INTENTIONAL MONOLITH  (read before splitting)                              ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   This is a deliberate single-file architecture. The design goals are:          ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   1. ZERO-FRICTION INSTALL — `python uais.py` is the only entry point.          ║
# ║      No package manager, no virtualenv, no import graph to untangle.            ║
# ║      Users on Raspberry Pi, air-gapped servers, or CI runners get the full      ║
# ║      system by copying exactly one file.                                         ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   2. SELF-CONTAINED AUDITABILITY — the entire system fits in one diff.          ║
# ║      Every security patch, every behavioural change is a single-file PR.        ║
# ║      No cross-package version skew. No "which version of uais-memory            ║
# ║      goes with this uais-agents?" problem.                                       ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   3. ATOMIC UPGRADES — `uais self-update` replaces one file.                    ║
# ║      Rollback is `cp uais.py.bak uais.py`. No migration scripts.                ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   4. INSTALLABLE PACKAGE SPLIT — first-class multi-team path:                   ║
# ║      `python uais.py install-packages` scaffolds a pip-installable monorepo:    ║
# ║      uais-core, uais-agents, uais-memory, uais-ml, uais-server, uais-skills,   ║
# ║      uais-channels, uais-cli. Each sub-package imports from this monolith as    ║
# ║      its seed implementation; extract modules incrementally from there.          ║
# ║      Packages are written to ~/.uais/packages/ on first run; then:              ║
# ║        pip install -e ~/.uais/packages/uais-cli   → gives `uais` system-wide   ║
# ║      USE THIS PATH whenever two or more people share the same codebase.         ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   5. SIZE IS INTENTIONAL — every section carries a § marker for grep/IDE nav.  ║
# ║      Run `grep "^# §" uais.py` for the full table of contents.                  ║
# ║      Sections are the unit of review; read one § at a time.                     ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   DO NOT split unless you have a concrete multi-team requirement.               ║
# ║   The install-packages command is the supported path when that time comes.      ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   🌀 SKILL GULPER — absorb any open-source skill into UAIS automatically       ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   UAIS can build its own skills from scratch OR ingest them from external       ║
# ║   skill markets and repositories without a dedicated marketplace.                ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   `python uais.py skill gulp URL`                                               ║
# ║      Fetches the URL (raw GitHub, GitLab, any HTTP), detects the format         ║
# ║      (SKILL.md · SOUL.md · external manifest · plain Markdown · Python),         ║
# ║      translates it to a UAIS SKILL.md, validates it through the sandbox,        ║
# ║      and hot-reloads it into the live skill index.  Works with:                 ║
# ║        • external skill packages (SOUL.md + tools/)                             ║
# ║        • external .yaml manifests                ║
# ║        • external skill directories (index.js auto-wrapped via skill_write)      ║
# ║        • TypeScript skills (transpiled prompt extracted)              ║
# ║        • Any Markdown file with a YAML frontmatter block                        ║
# ║        • Raw Python tool.py files (wrapped in a minimal SKILL.md)              ║
# ║      Imported skills are tagged with their source URL and version hash.         ║
# ║      Re-run the command to update; UAIS diffs and hot-swaps only changed files. ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ║   `python uais.py skill gulp-dir PATH`                                          ║
# ║      Recursively ingests every skill found under a local directory.             ║
# ║      Useful for bulk-importing a cloned skill hub or local skill library.       ║
# ║                                                                                  ║
# ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
# ║   USAGE                                                                          ║
# ║   python uais.py                     First run: probe → scaffold → guide       ║
# ║   python uais.py install             Install deps for detected hardware tier   ║
# ║   python uais.py install-packages    Extract pip-installable sub-packages ★   ║
# ║   python uais.py probe               Hardware tier, model, role info           ║
# ║   python uais.py models              Model registry for current tier           ║
# ║   python uais.py pull MODEL          Pull model via Ollama                     ║
# ║   python uais.py chat                Streaming interactive chat                ║
# ║   python uais.py chat --think        Chat with reasoning mode                  ║
# ║   python uais.py chat --role master  Run as master node                        ║
# ║   python uais.py agent "TASK"        TaskPipeline: plan→execute→critique       ║
# ║   python uais.py up [--port N]       FastAPI server + full web UI + MCP        ║
# ║   python uais.py up                  /healthz /readyz /metrics → probes        ║
# ║   python uais.py up                  /workflow-editor  → DAG visual editor     ║
# ║   python uais.py up                  /a2a/team-memory/ → team sync endpoints   ║
# ║   python uais.py keys                List API keys (managed via §AUTH)         ║
# ║   python uais.py audit verify        Verify audit log chain integrity          ║
# ║   python uais.py plugins             List hot-loaded plugins                   ║
# ║   python uais.py tui                 Textual TUI dashboard                     ║
# ║   python uais.py bench               Benchmark all available backends          ║
# ║   python uais.py eval                Behavioral eval harness (6 scenarios)     ║
# ║   python uais.py eval --save-baseline  Save current scores as baseline        ║
# ║   python uais.py eval --regression   Check scores vs baseline; exit 1 on drop ║
# ║   python uais.py decisions           Review pending tool-call decisions        ║
# ║   python uais.py decisions approve-all  Batch approve all pending             ║
# ║   python uais.py doctor              Pre-flight health check (all systems)     ║
# ║   python uais.py skill new NAME      Scaffold a new skill package              ║
# ║   python uais.py skill gulp URL      Ingest skill from any URL/marketplace     ║
# ║   python uais.py skill gulp-dir PATH Bulk-ingest all skills in a directory     ║
# ║   python uais.py workflows           List recent workflow states               ║
# ║   python uais.py workflows --id WF   Show detail for a workflow               ║
# ║   python uais.py scaffold            (Re)generate project workspace            ║
# ║   python uais.py channels            List/test messaging channel adapters      ║
# ║   python uais.py peers               List/probe known A2A peer agents          ║
# ║   python uais.py self-update         Pull latest release from GitHub           ║
# ║   python uais.py cost                Token cost report + per-task history      ║
# ║   python uais.py team                Team namespace info + shared memory stats ║
# ║   python uais.py memory export       Export memory bundle (AES-256-GCM)        ║
# ║   python uais.py memory import FILE  Import memory bundle (merge or replace)   ║
# ║   python uais.py export              Export full workspace as ZIP             ║
# ║   uais.py up                         /api/health/detail → full system health  ║
# ║   python uais.py import FILE         Import workspace from ZIP                ║
# ║   python uais.py sop                 List Standard Operating Procedures        ║
# ║   python uais.py eval --drift        Semantic drift check vs saved baseline    ║
# ║   python uais.py eval --save-baseline  Save current scores as drift baseline   ║
